ch.obermuhlner.jhuge.collection

Class ImmutableHugeHashMap<K,V>

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.AbstractMap<K,V>
      • ch.obermuhlner.jhuge.collection.AbstractHugeHashMap<K,V>
        • ch.obermuhlner.jhuge.collection.ImmutableHugeHashMap<K,V>
  • Type Parameters:
    K - the type of keys
    V - the type of values
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.util.Map<K,V>

    public class ImmutableHugeHashMap<K,V>
extends AbstractHugeHashMap<K,V>
    An immutable Map that stores elements in a MemoryManager.

    The mutating operations throw UnsupportedOperationException:

    • AbstractMap.put(Object, Object)
    • AbstractMap.putAll(Map)
    • AbstractMap.remove(Object)
    • clear()
    • Map.Entry.setValue(Object) on the entries in the entrySet
    • Iterator.remove() when iterating over the entrySet

    In order to create an ImmutableHugeHashMap you must add the elements in the ImmutableHugeHashMap.Builder.

    Other than the mutating operations all semantics, memory consumption and performance are identical to HugeHashMap.

    See Also:
    HugeHashMap
